				<blockquote class="messageText ugc baseHtml">
					
					I have a ZFS dataset where I keep all of my media: dvd&#039;s I&#039;ve ripped, music I&#039;ve purchased, software I&#039;ve downloaded, etc. This is shared over nfs, so I can mount it remotely at /var/media. So far so good.<br />
<br />
I installed the tranmission plugin. It downloads torrents, but here&#039;s where the problems begin:<br />
<br />
1) I can&#039;t get it to download to the &#039;media&#039; dataset that I have. I&#039;ve tried symlinks in both directions, and I get problems<br />
    a) If I put the symlink in my &#039;media&#039; dataset, my nfs mounts can&#039;t access them<br />
    b) If I put the symlink in the jail, transmission starts complaining<br />
<br />
2) As a slight aside, if I stop tranmission via the gui, I can&#039;t get it to start again. It simply complains that there is an error.<br />
<br />
How can I get transmission downloading into my &#039;media&#039; dataset so that it works over nfs? Thanks!
				</blockquote>
			</article>
			
			
